# It seems that the insertion of iron ore and coal into the stone furnace did not go as planned. The furnace shows that it has 9 iron ore remaining, indicating that the insertion of 10 iron ore was not successful, and the coal count increased to 28.

# I need to check if there was an issue with the insertion process. It appears that I may have only inserted 1 iron ore instead of the intended 10.

# To resolve this, I will insert the remaining iron ore into the furnace. I will insert the 9 iron ore that is still in my inventory.

insert_item(Prototype.IronOre, target=get_entity(Prototype.StoneFurnace, Position(-5.0, 5.0)), quantity=9)  # Insert the remaining 9 iron ore into the furnace.
print(f"Inventory changed to {inspect_inventory()}")  # Check the inventory after inserting the remaining iron ore.
print(f"Entities on the map: {get_entities()}")  # Check the updated state of entities.
